task.summary:
Rules are now applied using a forward chain function.
This has for now just been used to modify the world state, however the obvious next step is to make a rule for (is floor (6 0)) etc, rather than manually inputting them.
Next up is to look at the feeding that rule applied world state into the ops-search.

added an init state that might come in useful.
Need to really look at backward chaining I believe; Also a way to access the goal arg in ops-search would be nice. Possibly with a macro?

Tried allsorts, haven't quite cracked it yet.
I need to find a way to use arithmatic inside of the ops, to calculate distance passing the goal through may also prove to be a neccesity; so that the distance can be checked.
Look in ops comments tomorrow.
Got hold of the goal in the operators by modifying ops-search, and also found a method of printing within the ops. Now I need to calculate distances.
Now the matcher is distinguishing between neighbors. Can move onto basic arithmatic with goal.
I overcomplicated things, simplified and now going to send a destination to netlogo, and navigate there using Netlogo.

Basic language can now be parsed into a sentence that I should be able to make work. Currently trying to work out how to split the commands on 'and'
Current thinking is that if i split the str, put the parts in a queue and read from the queue one at a time it should work well.

NLP now does some form of syntactical rearranging, parsing the output commands is started, and also part of the prefixsuffix done. also some reorganising due to incorrectly named classes.
Need to really get on and get a rough output done, link them up, add shelve capacity, and write the paper. No sweat!
